Here we used Steadman’s Heat Index (HI)48 approach which combines ambient air temperature and relative humidity to estimate the heat stress. Steadman's field observations and measurements were translated into a table that showed heat stress values and the corresponding risk levels (Table 1). On the basis of the table generated by Steadman, Rothfusz (1990)49 developed the following equation for heat index.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
